    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Split Over Lyme Disease</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Diana Brest Toomey-Wilson letter urges everyong in medical field to stop fighting over Lyme disease diagnoses and work together for patients (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>After five years of receiving wrong diagnoses and being undertreated, I am keenly aware of the schism in managing Lyme disease and its effect of diverting resources from finding a cure. I hope the article ''Questioning Long-Term Lyme Cases'' (May 23) will embarrass doctors and licensing boards on both sides of the issue to quit fighting each other and finally begin working on the patient's behalf.</p>
        <p>DIANA BREST TOOMEY-WILSON  Norwalk, Conn.</p>
      </block>
